# Forward-reference targets for scripts/check-doc-xrefs.py.
#
# Each line is a glob (fnmatch) matched against the RESOLVED repo-relative path
# of a link target that does not exist yet. Listing a path here suppresses the
# "target not found" error for links that point at docs slated for a later
# sub-issue. `#` starts a comment (inline too); blank lines are ignored.
#
# These are EXPECTED-MISSING only. Once a target file lands, the ignore stops
# applying automatically (the checker validates the real file and its anchors);
# remove the corresponding line when that happens. Run with --strict to surface
# every still-missing forward-ref.
#
# Keep each entry as NARROW as possible — prefer the exact forthcoming file. A
# subtree glob (.../*) over a directory that already holds real docs silently
# masks a broken link into it, which is the failure mode this list is meant to
# avoid.

# --- Top-level docs/ subtrees (README scaffolding; populated across later phases) ---
docs/reference
docs/analysis
docs/operations

# --- Forthcoming design docs (one exact path each; add a line when a new ref lands) ---
docs/design/substrate/infrastructure/vdtid.md     # vdtid services/architecture — canon: vdti-area-vdtid-services.md
